Four different types of immigrants came to Sri Lanka, exiles, convicts, slaves and soldiers.
 
\subsubsection{Exiles}
In order to stay in control of the islands of the SEAA, the Dutch deported rebellious local regents to South Africa and Lanka. Lanka was preferred because it was closer to the SEAA. The Dutch had first taken possession of the former Portuguese colonies in the Moluccas and the lesser Sunda islands. By consequence, the first exiles came from there. In the late 17th century, there was a war of succession in Java. Following this, a number of Javanese princes were exiled to Lanka.

