\subsubsection{Free(d) Malays}
Particularly after the middle of the 18th century, the proportion of free Malay grew. Those were discharged soldiers and descendants of political exiles. There occupations included gardening rattan weaving, petty trade, domestic servants. The Malays counted as foreigners and had to perform \em Uliyam. \em Political exiles and soldiers were exempted]\citep[48f]{Hussainmiya1990}
 In 1769, the number of the `free' Malays was high enough to have an
own category for tax collecting purposes.\citep[9]{Bichsel}

